---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "GE Refrigerator Repair | Southern California | Haier-Owned Since 2016";
const description = "GE fridge repair across Southern California, French Door, side-by-side, bottom-freezer, Profile, Café, Monogram sub-brands. Same-day, $89 diagnostic waived. (424) 325-0520.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/ge-refrigerator-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is my GE fridge still made by General Electric, I thought I read Haier owns them now?",
    a: "Both things are true in a specific way. In June 2016, Haier (the Chinese home-appliance parent) acquired GE Appliances from General Electric for $5.6 billion. Since the acquisition, GE Appliances has operated independently from its Louisville, Kentucky headquarters under a long-term agreement with GE to continue using the GE brand name. So your GE-branded fridge is still badged GE, still manufactured and marketed under the GE name, still serviced through the GE Appliances parts and service network, it's just that the parent company is now Haier instead of General Electric. In practical service terms, the 2016 transition actually improved parts availability and distribution in the US because Haier invested in the Louisville operation and consolidated US distribution. The sub-brands, GE Profile, GE Café, GE Monogram, all operate under GE Appliances / Haier ownership too, and they have their own distinct service profiles covered on separate pages."
  },
  {
    q: "What's the difference between GE, GE Profile, GE Café, and GE Monogram, which page should I be reading?",
    a: "Four distinct tiers within the GE Appliances family, each with its own combo page. If your fridge is badged just \"GE\" (no sub-tier), you're on the right page, this covers the mainstream GE lineup. If your fridge is badged <b>GE Profile</b> (feature-focused premium, Full-Width Freezer Drawer, SmartHQ Wi-Fi), see <a href='/brands/ge-profile-refrigerator-repair/'>GE Profile refrigerator repair</a>. If it's badged <b>GE Café</b> (style-first premium, customizable brass / matte black / matte white handles, Keurig K-Cup option), see <a href='/brands/ge-cafe-refrigerator-repair/'>GE Café refrigerator repair</a>. If it's badged <b>GE Monogram</b> (ultra-luxury, column built-in, Statement Collection, $5K–$25K appliance range), see <a href='/brands/ge-monogram-refrigerator-repair/'>GE Monogram refrigerator repair</a>. The tier is on the exterior nameplate and on the model-number interior plate, easy to confirm before calling."
  },
  {
    q: "Which GE refrigerator models do you see most in LA?",
    a: "By volume, mainstream GE French-door models (GFE, GNE, GSS families in 25–28 cu ft capacity) dominate our GE service calls. GFE series French-door with ice + water dispenser is the single most-common GE install across LA mass-market households, Valley, San Gabriel Valley, South Bay, apartment-complex kitchens. GNE counter-depth French-door shows up in kitchen remodels where the standard-depth footprint won't fit. GSS side-by-side is the older-generation workhorse still present in many 2000s-2010s-era installed kitchens. Bottom-freezer GBE and top-freezer GTE are lower-volume but present. Apartment-compact GE models (smaller capacity, lower trim) appear in rental applications. For GE Profile / Café / Monogram sub-tier service volume, see those combo pages, all three sub-tiers represent substantial and growing LA service segments in premium kitchens."
  },
  {
    q: "GE fridge making water-dispenser noise or slow flow, what's the cause?",
    a: "Most common LA GE water-dispenser service pattern, especially on GFE French-door units. Diagnostic order: (1) water filter, LA's hard water accelerates filter scale and reduces flow; filter change and filter-housing cleaning $160–$260; (2) water-inlet valve, solenoid valve opens to admit water; failure modes are stuck-closed (no water) or leaking; valve swap $240–$380; (3) dispenser actuator switch or chute assembly, mechanical clicks but no water suggests actuator fault; $180–$280; (4) internal water-line freeze, especially in colder-garage kitchens where the supply line routes through the back wall; thaw + insulate $180–$260. Noise patterns on GE water dispensers typically trace to (2) or (3). We carry GE water-system parts in rotation since this is one of the highest-volume service items across the mainstream GE lineup."
  },
  {
    q: "GE fridge not cooling, is this the 2016 compressor generation issue?",
    a: "The context of your question matters. GE has a compressor warranty history around certain 2016-era French-door models, individual owners had variable experiences and GE provided repair support on affected units. Current service reality: if your GE fridge was manufactured in the 2015–2017 window and experiences sudden cooling failure, diagnostic should include verifying the compressor vs. start relay vs. capacitor vs. sealed-system leak. We check GE warranty status by serial number before any major compressor quote, GE Appliances service portal shows current coverage and any model-specific extended-warranty programs. Compressor replacement post-warranty $900–$1,500; start relay or capacitor swap (more common actual fault) $180–$280. Our techs explicitly don't default to compressor-failure diagnosis without ruling out the cheaper root causes first."
  },
  {
    q: "GE ice maker not making ice or making too little, is it the filter or the module?",
    a: "Both are possible; diagnostic separates them. Standard diagnostic order on GE ice makers: (1) verify water supply is reaching the ice maker, turn off the ice-maker arm, open water dispenser, confirm water flows (if no water at dispenser, problem is upstream: filter clog, inlet valve, or water-line freeze); (2) if water dispenser works but ice maker doesn't, the ice-maker module, fill valve, or temperature sensor is at fault; module swap $280–$440; (3) check freezer temperature, if freezer isn't cold enough (below 10°F), ice maker won't run at proper rate even when mechanically fine; underlying freezer temperature issue requires its own diagnostic; (4) assess ice production rate, partial production often points to filter scale or inlet valve, not module. LA's hard water accelerates filter and inlet-valve issues on all GE fridges; filter service $160–$260 is our first-line ice-maker preventive."
  },
  {
    q: "What does GE refrigerator repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic is $89, waived when you authorize the repair. Common mainstream GE bands: condenser coil clean + diagnostic $160–$260; water filter service + housing cleaning $160–$260; door gasket (French-door) $220–$380; ice-maker module $280–$440; water-inlet valve $240–$380; dispenser actuator / chute $180–$280; evaporator fan motor $280–$440; condenser fan motor $260–$420; defrost heater + thermostat $320–$480; damper door $240–$380; main control board $380–$580; compressor start/run capacitor $180–$280; compressor replacement (post-warranty) $900–$1,500. For GE Profile / Café / Monogram sub-tier pricing, see those respective combo pages, premium-tier service runs higher due to different parts sources. Mainstream GE parts inventory is the broadest in the US residential market, Haier's 2016 investment in the Louisville distribution consolidation improved availability substantially."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "LocalBusiness",
    "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair, GE Refrigerator Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical,
    "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL,
    "priceRange": "$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Service",
    "serviceType": "GE Refrigerator Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "GE refrigerator repair across Southern California, LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. Mainstream GFE French Door, GNE counter-depth, GSS side-by-side, GBE bottom-freezer, GTE top-freezer. GE Appliances (Haier-owned since 2016), Louisville KY operations. Sub-tier service at separate combos: GE Profile, GE Café, GE Monogram. $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": {
      "@type": "Offer",
      "priceSpecification": {
        "@type": "PriceSpecification",
        "price": "89.00",
        "priceCurrency": "USD",
        "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair"
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } }))
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "GE", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/ge/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "GE Refrigerator Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">
    {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (
      <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />
    ))}
  </Fragment>

  <div class="call-banner">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span>GE fridge not cooling or ice maker issue? Same-day service across LA:</span>
      <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
          <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › GE › Refrigerator Repair</div>
          <h1>GE Refrigerator Repair</h1>
          <p class="lede">
            GE Appliances is the Louisville, Kentucky-based home-appliance manufacturer that has been one of
            the largest US residential refrigerator brands for decades. Since June 2016, GE Appliances has
            been owned by Haier (the Chinese home-appliance parent) under a $5.6 billion acquisition that
            preserved GE branding and Louisville operations. The broader GE Appliances family covers four
            refrigerator tiers, mainstream GE (this page), feature-focused GE Profile, style-first GE
            Café, and ultra-luxury GE Monogram, each with its own combo page for tier-specific service
            details. Our techs service the full mainstream GE lineup across LA: GFE French Door, GNE
            counter-depth, GSS side-by-side, GBE bottom-freezer, GTE top-freezer. Same-day dispatch,
            $89 residential diagnostic waived with the repair.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-cta">
            <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
            <a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a>
          </div>
          <ul class="hero-facts">
            <li><b>GE Appliances Haier-owned since 2016</b>, Louisville KY operations, improved US parts network</li>
            <li><b>Four-tier GE family</b>, mainstream GE / Profile / Café / Monogram (each own combo page)</li>
            <li><b>Top-3 volume brand in LA</b>, deep parts inventory, first-visit repair priority</li>
            <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b>, waived when you authorize the repair</li>
          </ul>
        </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span>BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span>
      <span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span>
      <span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>GE across Southern California, the mainstream workhorse brand</h2>
      <p>
        GE Appliances has been one of the defining US residential refrigerator brands since the mid-20th
        century. The Louisville, Kentucky manufacturing and engineering operation has produced a broad
        mainstream lineup that's shipped to millions of US kitchens, apartments, rentals, and property-
        management portfolios. The 2016 Haier acquisition changed the ownership structure but preserved
        the GE brand, the Louisville headquarters, and the US service infrastructure, and in practical
        service terms actually improved US parts availability through Haier's distribution investment.
      </p>
      <p>
        The mainstream GE lineup (GFE, GNE, GSS, GBE, GTE families) serves the same market segment as
        mainstream Samsung and mainstream LG, mass-market and mid-market households, apartment installs,
        rental properties, multifamily buildings. Our GE service volume concentrates in exactly those
        geographies across all five counties: San Fernando Valley, San Gabriel Valley, South Bay,
        mid-market Westside kitchens, Pasadena, Koreatown and Central LA apartments, and East LA
        multifamily on the LA side; the central Orange County belt (Anaheim, Garden Grove, Santa Ana,
        Tustin, Fullerton); the Ventura mid-market (Oxnard, Ventura, Simi Valley, Camarillo); and
        the Inland Empire family-housing corridor (Ontario, Rancho Cucamonga, Riverside, Fontana,
        Moreno Valley, Murrieta, Corona). The three GE premium sub-
        tiers (Profile, Café, Monogram) each have distinct service profiles covered on their own combo
        pages, see the tier-disambiguation FAQ above for which page fits your fridge.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Mainstream GE refrigerator failures our techs see most often in LA</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        Pattern data from our mainstream GE service calls. Sub-tier (Profile / Café / Monogram) failure
        patterns are documented on those respective combo pages.
      </p>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Water-dispenser slow flow or noise, filter and inlet-valve service</h3>
        <p>
          Highest-volume mainstream GE service call. LA's hard water accelerates filter scale and inlet-
          valve wear. Diagnostic: filter service ($160–$260), then water-inlet valve ($240–$380), then
          dispenser actuator ($180–$280). Often combined with ice-maker service since both systems share
          the water-supply path.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Ice-maker module failure on GFE / GNE French-door</h3>
        <p>
          Ice-maker module swap at 6–10 years is one of our highest-volume mainstream GE services. Module
          $280–$440. Often preceded by reduced ice production over several months, worth diagnosing
          early since filter / inlet-valve service upstream may extend module life.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Fridge warm, freezer cold, evaporator fan or defrost system</h3>
        <p>
          Classic French-door symptom. Fan motor ($280–$440) first diagnostic target, then defrost heater
          + thermostat ($320–$480), damper door ($240–$380), control board ($380–$580). Our techs run
          through this order before quoting any sealed-system or compressor repair.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Door gasket compression loss, 6–10 year service</h3>
        <p>
          Mainstream GE door gaskets hold up well but lose seal quality at 6–10 years of daily use. Symptom:
          fridge runs continuously, condensation on exterior trim, frost buildup along door edge. Gasket
          replacement $220–$380 depending on model and door size.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Compressor start relay + capacitor on older units</h3>
        <p>
          Intermittent starting (clicking, compressor tries to start but cycles off) or complete start
          failure on mainstream GE units at 8–12 years points to start relay or run capacitor. Swap
          $180–$280. Common service, not a compressor replacement indicator.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>2015–2017 compressor service context</h3>
        <p>
          GE had a compressor warranty history on certain 2015–2017-era French-door models. We check GE
          warranty status by serial number before any major compressor quote. If your GE is in that
          manufacturing window and experiences sudden no-cool, the diagnostic includes verifying warranty
          coverage, GE may cover parts on affected units.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Mainstream GE refrigerator product lines we service</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        Current mainstream GE lineup spans French-door, side-by-side, bottom-freezer, and top-freezer
        configurations. Sub-tiers (Profile, Café, Monogram) have their own product lines and combo pages.
      </p>
      <div class="model-grid">
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>GFE French Door (volume platform)</h3>
          <p>GFE20, GFE24, GFE26, GFE28 families. 25–28 cu ft capacity, ice + water through-the-door
          dispenser, in-door water and ice. Single most-common mainstream GE fridge in LA.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>GNE counter-depth French Door</h3>
          <p>GNE25, GNE27 counter-depth variants for flush-to-cabinet installs. Kitchen-remodel
          applications. Same feature set as GFE with shallower depth profile.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>GSS side-by-side</h3>
          <p>GSS23, GSS25, GSS27 side-by-side families. Ice + water through-the-door, adjustable shelving.
          Older-generation workhorse still present in many 2000s-2010s kitchens.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>GBE bottom-freezer</h3>
          <p>GBE18, GBE21 bottom-freezer configurations. Freezer drawer below, fridge compartment above.
          Counter-depth options available. Common in kitchen refreshes and modern-layout preference
          kitchens.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>GTE top-freezer</h3>
          <p>GTE18, GTE21, GTE22 top-freezer configurations. Budget-through-mainstream tier. Common in
          rental properties and apartment installs alongside similar-tier Whirlpool and Roper.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Compact and specialty configurations</h3>
          <p>GE apartment-size and compact fridge configurations for smaller kitchens, ADU, and
          secondary-fridge applications. Beverage centers and under-counter specialty units.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>GE tier navigation, which combo page fits your fridge</h2>
      <p>
        GE Appliances markets four refrigerator tiers. Each has distinct service requirements. Use the
        exterior nameplate and the interior model-number plate to identify your tier, then go to the
        right combo page for tier-specific service detail.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>GE (mainstream)</b>, this page. GFE, GNE, GSS, GBE, GTE. Mass-market and mid-market
        households.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>GE Profile (feature-focused premium)</b>, Full-Width Freezer Drawer, SmartHQ Wi-Fi, advanced
        temperature-zone control. See <a href="/brands/ge-profile-refrigerator-repair/">GE Profile
        refrigerator repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>GE Café (style-first premium)</b>, customizable brass / matte black / matte white handles,
        Keurig K-Cup integrated fridge option, style-forward design. See
        <a href="/brands/ge-cafe-refrigerator-repair/">GE Café refrigerator repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>GE Monogram (ultra-luxury)</b>, column built-in, Statement Collection, Minimalist, panel-
        ready, $5K–$25K appliance range. See <a href="/brands/ge-monogram-refrigerator-repair/">GE
        Monogram refrigerator repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Haier Group also markets the Haier-branded compact / apartment lineup (different product family
        from GE Appliances), see <a href="/brands/haier-refrigerator-repair/">Haier refrigerator
        repair</a>. And Fisher &amp; Paykel + DCS are Haier-owned premium/integrated brands with their
        own service coverage, see <a href="/brands/fisher-paykel-refrigerator-repair/">F&amp;P
        refrigerator repair</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>What mainstream GE refrigerator repair costs in LA</h2>
      <p class="intro">Mainstream GE parts pricing runs at mass-market rates. Sub-tier pricing (Profile /
      Café / Monogram) is higher and documented on those combo pages. Residential diagnostic $89, waived
      with repair.</p>
      <table class="price-table">
        <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Residential diagnostic</td><td>$89</td><td>Flat, waived if repair is authorized same visit</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Condenser coil clean + diagnostic</td><td>$160 – $260</td><td>Preventive service</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Water filter + housing cleaning</td><td>$160 – $260</td><td>Hard-water SoCal preventive</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door gasket replacement (French-door)</td><td>$220 – $380</td><td>Two-door profile</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Ice-maker module</td><td>$280 – $440</td><td>Volume-platform service</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Water-inlet valve</td><td>$240 – $380</td><td>Dispenser + ice-maker path</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Dispenser actuator / chute</td><td>$180 – $280</td><td>Mechanical dispenser service</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Evaporator fan motor</td><td>$280 – $440</td><td>Freezer section</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Condenser fan motor</td><td>$260 – $420</td><td>Rear-bottom</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Defrost heater + thermostat</td><td>$320 – $480</td><td>Defrost-cycle repair</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Damper door</td><td>$240 – $380</td><td>Airflow regulator</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Main control board</td><td>$380 – $580</td><td>Electronic generations</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Compressor start / run capacitor</td><td>$180 – $280</td><td>8–12 year service</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Compressor replacement (post-warranty)</td><td>$900 – $1,500</td><td>Rare as root cause</td></tr>
      </table>
      <p class="small">
        Broader refrigerator cost reference: <a href="/price-list/refrigerator-repair-cost/">refrigerator
        repair cost guide</a>. Premium tier pages:
        <a href="/brands/ge-profile-refrigerator-repair/">Profile</a>,
        <a href="/brands/ge-cafe-refrigerator-repair/">Café</a>,
        <a href="/brands/ge-monogram-refrigerator-repair/">Monogram</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Service areas, where our GE calls come from</h2>
      <div class="area-grid">
        <div>
